Comparative Study of Multivariable Linear Regression

This project compares three implementations of multivariable linear regression for predicting median house prices using the California Housing dataset. The three methods are:

- Pure Python (using loops and lists)
- NumPy Vectorized Implementation
- Scikit-learn (using `LinearRegression`)

Dataset

 Dataset: California Housing Dataset
  Link: [https://www.dcc.fc.up.pt/\~ltorgo/Regression/cal\_housing.html](https://www.dcc.fc.up.pt/~ltorgo/Regression/cal_housing.html)
 Preprocessing:

  * Dropped missing values
  * Encoded `ocean_proximity` as integers
  * Normalized features using training set stats
  * Fixed random seed used for consistent train/test split

Evaluation Metrics

* Mean Absolute Error (MAE)
* Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE)
* R² Score
* Training/Convergence Time

How to Run
1. Install dependencies:
   pip install -r requirements.txt


2. Run each model:
   python pure_python_prob1.ipynb
   python numpy_prob2.py
   python sklearn_prob3.py


